        "description": "For over the past hundred years, there have been various official and unofficial lists of [top ten Chinese teas](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Chinese_teas#Ten_Famous_Teas), so if you combine all the different lists, it's a lot more than ten! Teas that have made the lists(s) include West Lake Dragon Well, Dongting Biluochun, Huangshan Maofeng, Lu Shan Cloud, Xinyang Maojian, Wuyi tea, Tieguanyin, and Keemun.\n\n**Characters**\n\n[中國](https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%E4%B8%AD%E5%9C%8B) means *China* or *Chinese*, [十](https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%E5%8D%81) is *ten*, [大](https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%E5%A4%A7) is *big*, [名](https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%E5%90%8D) is *name*, and [茶](https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%E8%8C%B6) is *tea*, so 中國十大名茶is *Chinese top ten big name teas*.",
